  "text": "A total of 2000 people were interviewed between May and June 2000 and included in the analysis. When compared with the random sample of Italian citizens, health consumers appeared to be somewhat older, more educated, more frequently located in Northern Italy and with more self-reported health conditions (table 1) . These differences are explained by the intrinsic characteristics of the samples (people seeking care versus healthy citizens) and by the methods of recruitment adopted (convenience versus random sampling), as reported fully in Methods, and in a previously published paper. [CITATION_1] The implications of these differences are fully discussed in the Discussion. Most cases (69%) required no help to fill in the questionnaire, and questions were read in 19% and explained in 12% of cases.",
